==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snakestone
<hw>Snake"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
kind of hone slate or whetstone obtained in Scotland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An ammonite; -- so called from
its form, which resembles that of a coiled snake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snake's-tongue</ent>⟦br⟧
